Role and responsibilities
Create software infrastructure using Java EE, which provides access to SQL and NoSQL storage, reliably manages job queues with switch-over and fail-over features, periodically collects information from networked systems in the Fab and offers big-data-like storage and computational capabilities;
Create on-site solutions that continuously monitors all scanners in a customer’s domain. The server can detect system failures before they happen and identify needed corrective actions.
Provide industrial automation tasks that take care of unattended complex adjustments to the manufacturing process, in order to enable highest yields in high volume manufacturing;
Implement and validate algorithms that give our customers the power to reach optimal results during manufacturing;
Create visualization and analytics applications for visual performance monitoring, which also help to sift through huge amounts of data to pinpoint potential issues and solutions. The analytics applications have a microservice based architecture with web micro-frontends connecting to the (restful) APIs of microservices deployed at the backend. The main frontend technologies are React, Redux and Saga. The main backend technologies are Java and Spring Boot.
Select and manage IT infrastructure that helps us run the software on a multi-blade server with plenty of storage. In this area, we use virtualization technologies (such as VM and Docker containers)Linux, Python and Splunk. In addition to Java.
Use emerging technologies to turn vision into reality, e.g. using big data and machine learning;

Your responsibilities:
Designing and implementing software, working on the product backlog defined by the Product Owner;
Ensuring the quality of personal deliverables by designing and implementing automated tests on unit and integration levels;
Cooperating with other teams to ensure consistent implementation of the architecture;- and agreeing on interfaces and timing of cross-team deliveries;
Troubleshooting, analyzing, and solving integration issues both from internal alpha and beta tests as well as those reported by our customers;
Writing or updating product documentation in accordance with company processes;
Suggesting improvements to our technical solutions and way of working, and implementing them in alignment with your team and their stakeholders

Education and experience
At least 4 years of Java SE or Java EE development experience;
Design and development of server-side software using object-oriented paradigm;
Creation of automated unit and integration tests using mocks and stubs;
Working with Continuous Integration;
Working as a part of a Scrum team.

If you’re applying for a junior position, you’ll need the following experience:
1 to 2 years of relevant Java experience- (i.e. Java SE/EE 1.8 or later);
Development of server-side software using object-oriented paradigm;
Creation of automated unit and integration tests using mocks and stubs;
Familiarity with Continuous Integration and Continuous Delivery;
Having knowledge of or already working as part of a Scrum team.

Skills
Knowledge of distributed computing systems, practical experience 
Experienced in build and release infrastructure, Maven, Nexus, Bamboo, GitHub 
Experience in Frontend development ReactJS, Redux, Saga 
Developed Microservices, considerable experience with Spring Boot 
Experience with database technologies such as SQL, MongoDB 
Experience with distributed message queues/logs such as Kafka, RabbitMQ 
Understand inter process communication and JVM peculiarities. 
Experienced Java EE developer, fluent in Java 8, Java 11 
Experience with modern technology introduction @ zero downtime including data migration 
Fan of automatic testing and qualification, if can be part of CI/CD pipeline.

Introduction to the job
Would you like to make impact on how our products are planned and delivered to customers?
Do you like to see problems as opportunities to solve?
Do you like to influence key decision makers in Business Line, Sales and Operations?


Let’s have a coffee together!


If yes, then you fit perfectly in our team!
We are looking for an experienced ASML colleague who can create and manage the best business plan by providing and executing the framework for effective decision making to deliver ASML growth.

Role and responsibilities
As an integrated business planner in our team you are responsible for the health of the Integrated Business Plan which you manage by mobilizing your network to mitigate risks and capture opportunities.

In this role you are responsible for approaching complex planning challenges from different angles and balance the interests of different stakeholders.

Together with Sales and Marketing departments you translate input from customers like Samsung, Intel, and TSMC into a demand plan. You will meet with product development teams of D&E to create product introduction plans. Together with Supply Chain Management, Manufacturing and Sourcing you will determine and validate planning parameters and create scenarios for the best production & capability plan for the horizon of the next 2~7 year. You will interact with and give advice to the Business Lines, Finance and other stakeholders. You will interface with and advice your IBP colleagues on long term planning aspects. You represent Integrated Business Planning in cross-sector improvement projects.

Besides delivering the best possible business plan including new product information and financials, you will be responsible for:
Ensuring that the complete organization is executing to the same plan;
Enabling decision making by reporting and presenting the various scenarios and its consequences to stakeholders and senior management;
Defining health indicators to monitor and manage on plan execution and progress;
Identifying and capturing opportunities, as well as identifying and mitigating risks;
Deploying the ASML business strategy and sustainable growth.

Education and experience
Master degree in Business/ Industrial engineering and management science, Finance, Supply Chain management or Business studies.

5+ years experience within ASML in the area of sales, finance, operations or program management;
Planning experience in large complex organizations, preferably in semicon field.

Skills
To thrive in this job, you’ll need the following skills:

Challenges people and solutions;
Leadership skills;
Seen as authority in planning disciplines;
Persistent entrepreneur with business sense;
Self-assured, charismatic and capable of convincing people;
Strong analytic capability and a pro-active initiating attitude;
Capable to make deep-dive analyses while maintaining high-level overview;
Team player with good social skills;
Strong communicator in English.


Other information
The Integrated Business Planner is part of the Integrated Business Planning department which is a separate entity within the Operations sector with a strong interface with Business Lines. Its independent role is used to create an objective decision making process for planning purposes across ASML. It plays a vital role in bringing parts of information together, providing the right decisions and consequences to senior management and board level. Extensive contact with various sectors within ASML is required to be able to make the right links.
Integrated Business Planning is a young, social and dynamic team of 25 professionals that likes to give a warm welcome to a new team member.

